According to my understanding the dictEnabledColumn checks if columns are dictionary supported and not raw indexed through createDictionaryForColumn method. In json and text indexes we are not enabling dictionary support when optimizeDictionary is set as they are high cardinal types. So in such case, I feel this condition should be !originalConfig.getConfig(StandardIndexes.inverted()).isEnabled() || !dictEnabledColumn

@npawar @jadami10 correct me if my analysis is wrong here.

